                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 117</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Following his attendance at the Seventh Session of the North Atlantic Council in
                    Ottawa, September 15–20, <persName corresp="#p_DG1">Alcide De
                    Gasperi</persName>, Prime Minister of Italy, arrived in Washington on September
                    24 for 3 days of meetings with the President, the Secretary of State, and
                    Department of State officials. One of the major subjects discussed was the
                    question of Trieste which was the focus of the first meeting with the Secretary
                    of State during the afternoon of September 24 and was also raised by <persName
                        corresp="#p_DG1">De Gasperi</persName> during his talk with President
                        <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> at noon on September 25. For
                    the minutes of these meetings, see Documents 309 ff.</p>
            </div>
